http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/VIT%E2%80%99s-three-day-carnival-returns/article14539065.ece

 ‘Engineering for changing lives’ will be the theme for the eighth edition of graVITas’ 16, a carnival which will be held by the VIT University, Vellore, from September 23 to 25.With about 30,000 participants, the event will have a host of programmes, including ‘Robowars’, ‘Contraption’, and ‘RC Drag racing’; there will also be a stand up comedy.This three-day festival will have 20 premium events, 80 technical events, and 38 workshops where prizes estimated at Rs. 21 lakh will be distributed, according to a release.